Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.84,0:00:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,– So maybe the Nomad got away, but at least we know he's- 
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.93,0:00:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,– Not. Now.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.09,0:00:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,They're lined up early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.42,0:01:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.26,0:01:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to pay for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.54,0:01:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Rules are rules.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.37,0:01:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Captain Toth, Don Paragon awaits your report.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.66,0:01:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet he's gonna be happy to see us.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.35,0:01:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Toth! You're back.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.94,0:01:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a leg hair plucking to {\i1}vamanos{\i0} to so let's just jump to the part
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.92,0:01:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,where you didn't find the Nomad and you vow to continue your never-ending quest - yada, yada, yada.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.14,0:01:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We found him.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.15,0:01:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.88,0:01:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We found the Nomad.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.93,0:02:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You {\i1}found{\i0} Nomad?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Toth! I could just devour you, you beautiful bronze statue!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.33,0:02:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So where is he? I gotta see my magical little meal ticket!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.90,0:02:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.16,0:02:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.47,0:02:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Lost the Nomad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.22,0:02:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,He escaped, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.91,0:02:26.62,Default,,0,0,0,,His magic was as crafty as the legend said.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.75,0:02:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,He might have gotten away, But I'd like to think we learned the value of teamwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.72,0:02:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, except in the part where Toth stomped off on her own there at the end and kind of left everybody back at the-
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.87,0:02:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,What Skout means to say is now that we've seen what he can do we'll be better prepared for the next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.05,0:02:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dramatic! Harrowing tragic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.76,0:02:51.61,Default,,0,0,0,,A fiery escape! Dreams up in smoke! I love it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.61,0:02:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.48,0:02:56.33,Default,,0,0,0,,But progress is still progress.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And this was definitely progress, despite your defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.88,0:03:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Every noble venture is bound to endure setbacks
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.52,0:03:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's like that thing I always say about myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.26,0:03:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in the early days of the Oasis, when I bravely endeavored to stumble upon the only water source for miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.12,0:03:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to establish my very own highfalutin utopia,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.54,0:03:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what was my most important quality?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.05,0:03:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, you in the front.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.83,0:03:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Persistence?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.16,0:03:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Looking sharp?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.30,0:03:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A modest loan with a reasonable interest rate?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.67,0:03:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Being first!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is exactly what we're going to do now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to nab that magical monster before anyone else can get their grubby little hands on him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.18,0:03:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The question is: How do we do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.98,0:03:42.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I suggest regrouping immediately and-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.59,0:03:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Might Red Manuel offer a different suggestion?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.96,0:03:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, you're Red Manuel...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.20,0:03:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a shtick, third-person, I love it. Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.24,0:03:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why thank you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.37,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,– it's nice to be appreciated for-
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.64,0:03:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,– Continue.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:03:59.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.00,0:04:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Why worry about being first when you can pay someone else to be first for you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.22,0:04:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not following here, Rojo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.22,0:04:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,With your many resources and vast influence, you could offer a reward for the Nomad's capture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.76,0:04:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,The Southwest has many bounty hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.53,0:04:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We could cover much more ground in the search for the Nomad rather than putting all our huevos in one basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.95,0:04:25.29,Default,,0,0,0,,A very unworthy basket.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, I think Red is still dealing with a concussion from his spectacular failure on our mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.84,0:04:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no no, I like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.96,0:04:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll give them money, water, a time-share, whatever gets me the Nomad before anybody else realizes how valuable he is.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.43,0:04:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Rojo here has a point, Toth,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.74,0:04:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and I do love huevos...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.84,0:04:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I can find him. You need to- 
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.04,0:04:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What I {\i1}need{\i0} is to be certain {\i1}you{\i0} can do your job, Toth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.28,0:04:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Because right now, I've got more doubts than I have fancy outfits, and I have a lot of fancy outfits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.34,0:05:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something that needs attending on the outskirts,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.22,0:05:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,just the sort of rough-and-tumble mission to get you back on track, chica.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.63,0:05:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And don't go looking for the Nomad until you prove you can be useful.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.23,0:05:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.01,0:05:16.56,Default,,0,0,0,,May the best man win.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.23,0:05:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,First things first.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.52,0:05:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I want new wanted posters in every town from here to the Iron Border featuring my reward.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.74,0:05:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And let's make sure it's got that "Don Paragon Pizzazz".
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.47,0:05:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Mister Paragon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.04,0:05:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,not to be too prickly about it, but,...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.45,0:05:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,...the Nomad saved us all. He came back for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.10,0:05:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he didn't want us to die. 
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.90,0:05:39.58,Default,,0,0,0,,A moral compass.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.58,0:05:41.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just splendid, Skout.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.32,0:05:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That means he's got a weakness, good thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.20,0:05:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What? No, that's not what I meant, I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.60,0:05:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Why we gotta catch him so bad?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.58,0:05:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Because El Rey wants him, little wildflower. That's the thing about being the king,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.60,0:05:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you get whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.30,0:05:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, who are we to second guess?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.81,0:06:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you know more about the dangers of magic than El Rey?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.05,0:06:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Me neither.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.30,0:06:07.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, now, cheer up, Captain Toth!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.14,0:06:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The wasteland is a treacherous place that fairer folk can't brave on their own.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.92,0:06:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,With any luck he won't have gotten far.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.78,0:06:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The elements will have undoubtedly slowed him to a pathetic crawl.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.02,0:07:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.82,0:07:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you. You proselytizing? Tryin' to sling me some ballyhoo?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.76,0:07:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The silent sell, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.70,0:07:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't seen that one before.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.84,0:07:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Who's there?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know Martha, he won't tell me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.08,0:07:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's crafty...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.84,0:07:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}'s he some door-to-door trickster?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.12,0:07:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Tell him we don't want no more magazine subscriptions.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.10,0:07:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We can't even read!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.71,0:07:38.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear that, snake? We're poor and illiterate!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.03,0:07:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Joke's on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.82,0:07:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi, you're new around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.43,0:07:56.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Name's Barty. Wanna join an exciting project to help Bliss Hill?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.92,0:08:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! But first you have to answer my exhaustive questionnaire.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.00,0:08:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.82,0:08:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Ever killed a man?\NKnow your basic 'rithmetics?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.06,0:08:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you believe in ghosts?\NCan you do a cartwheel?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.33,0:08:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... form could have been better.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.48,0:08:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, I just noticed something. Can't you talk?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.00,0:08:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,A mute! That's good for diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.54,0:08:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, last question, and the most important.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.16,0:08:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Got any food? Or water?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.70,0:08:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Guess that was hoping for too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.59,0:08:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So no food, no water, ain't never killed a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.94,0:08:35.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What can you do?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.93,0:08:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow! You can do bonafide magic! What other tricks you got?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.86,0:08:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the one, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.21,0:08:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I ain't one to complain, especially since we got this dancing fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.99,0:09:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if that ain't this town in a nutshell, I don't know what is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.26,0:09:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know what? I think you passed the test, stranger. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.76,0:09:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Magic, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.03,0:09:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm... they're either here or at Merry Caverns.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold up a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.28,0:09:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Barty, why'd you bring a stranger here? Are you under duress?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.06,0:09:33.33,Default,,0,0,0,,He's using the secret code!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.33,0:09:34.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What's he saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.31,0:09:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Either he has to go to the bathroom or...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.46,0:09:40.04,Default,,0,0,0,,...Operation Bandit!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.04,0:09:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Consult the protocols.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.00,0:09:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, section 14, article C: "Bandits"
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.61,0:09:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,There are three types of bandits.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.14,0:09:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The etymology of the word 'Bandit' comes from the Vocaran word 'Bandito' which-
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.23,0:09:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on Eugene, my shooting arm's getting tired!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.02,0:09:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no protocal for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.70,0:10:02.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Another victim of bureaucracy! Curse all this red tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.60,0:10:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Stuff it, Eugene. Why'd you bring him here anyway, Barty?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.53,0:10:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Just show them what you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes... baby rocks?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.70,0:10:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My Pappy's birds and bees talk didn't cover this at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.07,0:10:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you dolts. He brings things to life with magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.96,0:10:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.14,0:10:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Stranger, it's time I told you the purpose of this outfit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.72,0:10:31.78,Default,,0,0,0,,We're...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.16,0:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mill Preservation Society!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.68,0:10:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All them long-legged grown-ups forgot about the mill when the water stopped flowing.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.40,0:10:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're the future of this here town, and we're gonna do whatever we can to get that mill turning again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.99,0:10:48.02,Default,,0,0,0,,To heck with the grown-up establishment, our livelihoods depend on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.02,0:10:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We ain't hooli-gans, we're hooli-cans!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.48,0:10:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And we's gonna fix Bliss Hill!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.99,0:10:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that mean you're with us?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.54,0:10:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Here they are, sheriff.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.21,0:11:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold it right there, long-legs!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.11,0:11:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Barty. Somehow I knew I'd find out you were the reason for these dunderheads complaining.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.24,0:11:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Looks like my fool boy led you lot on a goose chase.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.72,0:11:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ain't no magic here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.49,0:11:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,That's only gonna bring us more problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.96,0:11:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But Pa, he is doing magic and it ain't bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.72,0:11:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Stranger, I'm only gonna say this once.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.44,0:11:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your dark magic and get out of here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.94,0:11:28.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He ain't a stranger, he's my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.05,0:11:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,His magic can help whole town.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.95,0:11:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, he's gonna bring back the old mill.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.20,0:11:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why not? You brought the rocks to life!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.42,0:11:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you can do it, Bliss Hill needs you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.96,0:11:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Barty, get away from him!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.32,0:11:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just let him try. It could change everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.00,0:11:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what anybody says about magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.71,0:12:06.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright Barty, time to run along-
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.28,0:12:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See Pa, it's working! I knew he could do it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.40,0:12:21.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you had a few screws loose, Barty, but this is bad medicine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.62,0:12:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't have the mill acting on its own like this. It'll bring the wrong sorts to Bliss Hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.36,0:12:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You broke it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.45,0:12:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lucky I don't string you up right where you stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.81,0:12:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Get out of here. Don't {\i1}never{\i0} come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.76,0:13:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't see that every day.
